// DEPRECATED — DO NOT DEPLOY FROM THIS REPO.
//
// The live Firestore rules for the `propagentic-crm` project are owned by
// the propagentic-web repo:
//
//   Propagentic-web / branch live-main / crm.firestore.rules
//
// Deploy with (run from the propagentic-web repo, NOT this one):
//
//   firebase deploy --only firestore:rules \
//     --project propagentic-crm \
//     --config firebase.crm.json
//
// This file is intentionally an INVALID rules stub. If `firebase deploy`
// from this repo accidentally targets `firestore:rules`, it will fail to
// compile (no `service cloud.firestore { ... }` block) rather than
// silently clobber the live rule set.
//
// Why this matters: a previous stub here granted blanket read+write to
// any `@propagenticai.com` account. Deploying it would have (1) locked
// out non-`@propagenticai.com` allowlisted accounts (weinba23@wfu.edu,
// brantleyryan03@gmail.com), (2) made the bulk-ingested catalogs
// (regions/owners/parcels) client-writable, and (3) widened the Kanban
// collections from super_admin-only to @propagenticai.com-wide.
